description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regional Advancing Practice Supervision and Assessment Lead (Primary Care AP) HEE SW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Will be considered as &lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt; or a &lt;strong&gt;Secondment for up to 36 months&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Long-Term Plan calls for a step change in advancing practice requiring capacity to be built at national, regional and sub-regional level, e.g. in Sustainability and Transformation Partnerships (STPs)/Integrated Care Systems (ICSs) or ‘faculties’ to drive changed. HEE’s National Centre for Advancing Practice has been established to standardise routes into advanced practice, accredit advanced practice programmes and recognise registered health and care practitioners who demonstrate the capabilities set out in the advancing practice or consultant practitioner framework and in the national education standards for advancing practice. The provision of high-quality supervision to multi-professional advanced practice learners is essential to improving outcomes for learners and patients by enabling the development of clinical mastery in practice. The Centre will also set &lt;em&gt;national best practice guidance standards/principles for advancing practice supervision&lt;/em&gt; and will recognise and accredit supervisors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health Education England South West is looking for an experienced Primary Care Advanced Practitioner for the post of &lt;strong&gt;Advancing Practice Supervision and Assessment Lead (Primary Care AP) - Faculty of Advancing Practice HEE SW&lt;/strong&gt;. This is one of several vacancies across HEE regionally to provide an interface between HEE’s new national &lt;strong&gt;Centre for Advancing Practice and &lt;/strong&gt;the local system. (The Centre has been established to standardise routes into advanced practice, accredit advanced practice programmes and recognise registered health and care practitioners who demonstrate prerequisite capabilities in advancing practice).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will support the Regional Faculty Lead in Advancing Practice in delivering a wide range of functions that ensures the successful implementation of advancing practice at regional and sub-regional level within Primary Care AP Roles (Nursing/MSK/Paramedic). This is an evolving role integrally linked to the wider workforce transformation agenda, innovation in curricula development and workforce wellbeing strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will have proven leadership capability, extensive clinical experience at an advanced practice level and of working in multi-professional teams. They will be an experienced clinical educator, with relevant and up-to-date training in recruitment, supervision, assessment and equality and diversity and have an academic interest in training and education across primary and secondary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves working with internal and external regional stakeholders (e.g. education providers, system leads, service providers, Heads of School/Training Programme Directors (TPDs), professional leads and other Post Graduate Medical and Dental Education (PGMDE) team members) and specifically the Primary Care Training Hubs to ensure all learners have robust supervision in line with the Centre’s guidance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with the Centre, Regional Faculty Lead and other Supervision &amp; Assessment Leads within the Faculty they will help shape and implement robust, standardised and quality assured processes to support the recruitment, selection and assessment of advanced practice learners to ensure they are fit for the development of clinical mastery in practice. They will ensure processes are documented, roles and responsibilities are clearly defined and oversee their ongoing and sustained delivery. They will also offer guidance to learners and listen to, and act upon, concerns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be professionally and managerially accountable to the Regional Faculty Lead for Advancing Practice. Although the main focus of this role is to lead and develop the supervision and assessment for the Faculty, as a senior clinician/manager, the post holder may have wider roles and projects as agreed with the Faculty Lead that support local and national initiatives. This job description and personal specification is therefore only an outline of the tasks, responsibilities and outcomes required of the role. The job holder will carry out any other duties as may reasonably be required by their line manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job description and person specification may be reviewed on an ongoing basis in accordance with the changing needs of HEE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based in the HEE regional office in Bristol or Plymouth and under normal circumstances will require frequent travel throughout the region and sometimes nationally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will commence at the bottom of Band 8b with a full-time starting salary of £53,168, with a pay step increase after 5 years’ service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These salaries are offered in accordance with NHS Terms and Conditions and the HEE Pay Progression Policy and are subject to annual cost of living review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a South West based post - when we are able to return to an office based environment, the primary location for the successful candidate will either be Park House, Bristol, or Plumer House, Plymouth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will generally work remotely, using MS Teams, following current NHS Guidance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For applications on a secondment basis, agreement should be obtained from the employer prior to submitting the application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you like what you have read and think you have the skills and experience we need then don&#39;t delay, apply today! We get lots of applications for our roles and so we sometimes have to close our posts early. Don&#39;t miss out! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Munro-Davies, Associate Postgraduate Dean for Workforce Transformation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: Lisa.Munro-Davies@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
